                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The basements, imo, are the best.  Just don't ever go to Back Left area, stuff there is just insane.  Red and Yellows to 65th, most see invis... /shudder
<br />

<br />
The only things I can think of that are charmable are the humans and the Wrulons.  I prefer Humans.  Oh and the Sentrys aren't snareable or rootable, so they suck as pets.  Also, sentrys are higher level than the other human types, except for nameds.  Guards and Guardians are great though.
<br />

<br />
The black armors aren't rootable or snareable, except for one who spawns in Front Left Basement, in the room with the humans.  He is for some reason, even though he has the same name as the ones in the room just before his who aren't snareable/rootable.
<br />

<br />
The white armors, while rare, are rootable/snareable and seem to drop loot more often than any others.  They summon though so keep them rooted so they'll pound on your pet and not summon you.
<br />

<br />
Basically get in one of the basements, on the one wall that has no mobs.  Pacify one of the pairs and tash the other from max range.  Charm him and set him to guard.  Then root his buddy, tash and slow him, then sick pet on him.  Don't forget to do at least 1 point of damage so you'll get more exp.  There are 3 pairs per big room, 2 pairs per smaller room, and I'm not talking about the big rooms with the armors, I'd stay clear of those until you had this all down.
<br />

<br />
Edit: forgot the shrines, they're good also but have less 'running around room' than the basements.  The south most shrine is my favorite one.  Lot of pops and there's a yellow con NPC that often pops that is great exp.  He's rootable/snareable and summons, so keep him rooted.
<br />

<br />
Pretty much anywhere that has human types that con blue to 65th level is doable for exp in HoH.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
