                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I've been all over HoH and I have yet to find any spot that is better then the 'left hero shrine'(if its called that, its just known as the 'hero shrine' on my server, the other one(or are there more?) is not viable) .
<br />

<br />
It has the highest number of mobs, 3 in each back room, 2 in each entrace to those back room, 4 at the entrance, and 2 hero shrine guardians that 'trigger' themselves every once in awhile.
<br />

<br />
16 mobs right there, people say that there isn't enough room to move around in the hero shrine, I disagree, the advantage of the hero shrine is that mobs run in 'rails' which allow you to run out of the way of the 'rail' and be EXACTLY 1 step away from melee, long enough to run past, and gain advantage(using the little space to the left and right in the middle hall and the horizontal hall)and be able to get distance to cast root-charm-mezz.
<br />

<br />
The basements on the other hand have mobs running straight for you, no matter how good your evasive maneuvers are you will have the mob running straight for you and the only way to get distance is to run in a straight line and hope that there is enough room to get distance to cast.
<br />

<br />
Second advantage, there aren't 16 mobs in any other one of the camps(that are rootable).
<br />

<br />
Anywho, I would strongly recommend this spot for any CoD enchanter... I can break 1 AA in 45 min easy, and my gear is horrid for 'pvm'</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />'I learned long ago to cover my back and attack from behind'
<br />

<br />
               -- Cidolfas Orlandu</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
