                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">If you want to try it out with more safety (imo) then I'd go to either front right, back right, or front left basement.  Not sure of the locs but if you have LoY maps downloaded then back right is where the map has red on it, all 3 rooms of back right basement are the red ones.  The bottom right corner of the map (SE corner of the zone) is Front Left Basement.  The front right basement is NE corner of the zone.  
<br />

<br />
If you don't have the maps, then just go out into HoH and follow the big path around.  If you want to go to front right, go back and take the first right follow it around til you come to a 'T'.  Go right and follow the big path around til it ends you up at some steps.  Go up the steps and down into the basement into the back area there.  For front left basement just go the opposite way.
<br />

<br />
If you want a shrine, just go back and go left and at the 'T' go left and the first building to your right that you can go into is the Left shrine (or South Shrine depending on what it's called on your server).  
<br />

<br />
There's only 4 places to worry about See Invis mobs, from what I've seen:
<br />
1- The DC pets near zone in sometimes see invis.  Just go between them all without getting close to any of them and you'll be fine.
<br />

<br />
2- The South Shrine sometimes has an outside guard that sees invis.  It's rare but it's happened.
<br />

<br />
3- When entering the Front Left Basement, there are a ton of White Armors.  Sometimes one or 2 of them will see invis.  Con them all and go the way there aren't see invis mobs.
<br />

<br />
4- The Back left area is just full of See Invis mobs.  Stuff back there is yellow/red to 65th anyway and I've been on 18 member raids that wiped here, it's hard stuff.
<br />

<br />
If there are more see invis areas I haven't ran across them, so it's really easy to just put up Improved Invis and wander all over this zone, as long as you watch those 4 areas.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
