                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hey all,
<br />

<br />
I wrote this up for a guild mate, but may as well post it here for everyone's benefit...
<br />

<br />
Spell line up I use
<br />

<br />
Command of Druzzil
<br />
Sleep / Bliss
<br />
Howl of Tashan
<br />
Pacification
<br />
Speed of Vallon
<br />
Arcane Rune
<br />
Forlorn Deeds
<br />
Greater Fetter
<br />

<br />
I swap in Bliss only if one of the "named" guys is up.  Don't get excited, they rarely drop anything, and if they do, it might be a spec parchment.
<br />

<br />
Things to note:
<br />
The named guys cannot be rooted/snared
<br />
A Valorian Sentry cannot be rooted/snared
<br />

<br />
Things to have:
<br />
Ceramic Blue Band (CBB)
<br />
Ext Range 4 item (not necessary, but bloody helpful).
<br />
Sow Potions
<br />

<br />
Getting to the spot (it's called Hero Hall on our server.  Other servers call it South Shrine).  Invis up and run to...
<br />

<br />
<img src="http://www.pobox.com/~izzuyen/hoh1.jpg" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
Buff yourself up with Maelin, CHA, VoQ, etc.  Have a Virtue if you can too.  Makes you last longer if charm breaks (more on that later).
<br />

<br />
Layout of the mobs once you get there:-
<br />

<br />
<img src="http://www.pobox.com/~izzuyen/hoh2.jpg" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
For your first pet, you want to pull either 1 or 7.  Just pacify the other, then tash.  Soon as tash lands, run down to the end of the corridor towards where 2, 3 etc are.  When you hit the wall at the end, start casting CoD.  It will land just before you get hit.  Ext range 4 makes this a bit safer.  With SoW on, you are fast enough to get enough distance between you and the mob for CoD's cast time.
<br />

<br />
Guard your pet, and haste him.
<br />

<br />
Pacify either 2 or 3, and pull the other with tash, then root him with Greater Fetter.  There is enough time in the spell cast recycle for your spells to come back up, and for you to cast root before he gets within melee range of you.
<br />

<br />
Slow him, then send in pet.
<br />

<br />
Dangers at this point:-
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Whilst you are pulling, rooting and slowing your first kill, you are standing next to a hasted mob that can double for 544.  Nervous yet? <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="icon_biggrin.gif" border="0" /></span>
<br />

<br />
Tap the kill mob with your ceramic blue band (works from inventory).  This does 5 points of DD dmg and a few points of DoT dmg.  Enough so that you get the most xp you can from the kill.
<br />

<br />
Wait till the mob dies.  When you get more confident doing this, you can start to prep the next mob at around 30% of your current target.  Doing that maximizes your charm duration to clear all 6 on one "side" and have enough charm duration left to park your pet whilst you prep to kill him (more on that later).
<br />

<br />
For killing the other 2 or 3 mob, just cast root, tash then slow, and send in pet where he is.  This applies to all the remaining mobs on the side (4, 5 and 6).  In the main room area (where 4 5 and 6 are), none of the others will agro whilst you are killing one at it's spawn point (just don't kill 6 first).
<br />

<br />
Once you have finished one "side", go pull 7 with tash, make him your pet and rinse/repeat for the other side.
<br />

<br />
When the mobs respawn, 1 and 7 will respawn last (they were the last to die on each side) so you will have to pull your pet from 2/3 or 8/9.  Same tactic applies, but you can just run to the middle of the long corridor to get enough distance for charm to land.
<br />

<br />
If it gets too far out of sync for your comfort, just sit in the middle (the safe area that the line on the first map leads you to) and wait for everything to respawn.  I still do that on occasion to give myself a break.
<br />

<br />
Handling Sentries:-
<br />

<br />
If any of the mobs you are going to kill is a sentry, here is what to do.  Send in pet straight away, and cast slow.  Hopefully slow will land.  If not, tash and re-slow.  Your pet will take a bit of dmg, so it can be worthwhile making up the balance by nuking a few times with Insanity.  Depends on your mana pool.
<br />

<br />
If you have 2 sentries facing each other, pacify one, pull the other with tash, and then mez it with Sleep.  Then do your prep (slow, etc) and send in pet.  You will find that the Sentry chases you.  In HoH, this is easy to overcome.  In one of the alcove areas in the main corridor, just start running large circles.  Your pet will be able to hit the Sentry whilst it is chasing you, and eventually your pet will gain agro.  That allows you to back off a bit and med, and also do your CBB tap (never ever forget that).
<br />

<br />
Handling named:-
<br />

<br />
If you get a named spawn (will always be in either spot 6 or 12) clear as normal.  Then just before him, drag your pet out, guard him somewhere, then camp out.  That will break charm and clear agro.  Your pet will go back to his spawn point and regen full health (which he will need).  When you get back in, recharm your now full health pet, and kill the named as though he were a Sentry.  Remember to put Bliss up for charm break here.
<br />

<br />
As you get more experienced, you can also break the charm on your current pet (who should be low health by this time) root him, slow him (he is still tashed, then go pull another pet from the two Hero Shrine Guardians (the un-numbered mobs on the second map).  Use the new pet to finish off your old, then send in to the named.  At the end of the named fight, your pet will be low health (those named hit hard), enabling you to do the "finish em off" tactic (see below).
<br />

<br />
Charm breaks:-
<br />

<br />
Charm always breaks at the worst time.  Worst for me was finishing off one mob, having the second prep'd, and a respawn behind me.  Charm broke, both roots broke, and I had to run past the respawn to give myself room to recover.  I came out of that mess with 2% health, and all 4 dead.  What I'm not mentioning is the other times when I have ended up a small smear on the ground <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="icon_biggrin.gif" border="0" />  It does happen, it will happen.  Get used to it, and don't give up.  Once you get good at this, death will be rare.
<br />

<br />
Be alert for a charm break, and always make sure you have a reasonable amount of distance between you and the fight.  When charm breaks, stand up, target your now ex-pet (the kill mob should still be rooted), and start running.  Run to the other end of the main corridor, and when you hit the wall, cast charm.  Your pet should be out of range.  Just keep spamming that button till the cast starts.  If you don't have room to run, use mez instead.  I don't like to use mez unless absolutely necessary because it has a chance of a mem blur and if the pet forgets about you, you now have a full health pet.  That can **** up your finishing off tactic (more later).
<br />

<br />
If you are fighting a Sentry and charm breaks, you will need to find room to slap a mez on that sentry.  Otherwise you have problems.  I'll leave it to you to figure out how to do that.  Nothing works like practice, and I can't cover all situations for you here.
<br />

<br />
Finishing off your pet:-
<br />

<br />
You've killed number 6 (or 12), and it's time for the pet to die.  He should be low health at this stage.  Eventually you will get a feel for his health, and be able to time your slow on mob 6 to allow mob 6 to beat your pet up a little more to make finishing him off easier.
<br />

<br />
During the mob 6 fight, guard the pet and move to the entryway for the room.  Mem up Strangle, Torment of Scio, Insanity and Improved Invis.  Once the fight is over, target pet and cast Imp Invis.  Pet starts running towards you.  Root him when he is in range.  Slap on Torment and Strangle (watch that DD component, it might break your root, and remember he is still hasted).  Let his health get down to about 4 - 5%, then Insanity him.  That should finish him off for full xp for you (about 5% AA xp on that one kill).
<br />

<br />
XP to be gained:-
<br />

<br />
I have TD2, FT7, MC3 and my CHA is at 280 with CHA buff up.  With C5 up, and barring excessive charm breaks, I can clear all 12 mobs and have 60% mana remaining before respawns start.  With zero charm breaks, I can walk away with 90% mana.  Total time to kill all 12 without charm breaking is about 16 minutes (which matches nicely with the ~20min or so respawn).  At 100% to AA, you should be getting around 3% per normal kill and 5% per pet kill.  All up, on a good run you can get an AA every 45 minutes or so.  That slows down if you get excessive charm breaks (very rarely happens to me with TD2).
<br />

<br />
Go forth and gather those AA's my friends <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="icon_biggrin.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
Regards,
<br />

<br />
CJ
<br />

