                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Thanks <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
As to WoM... put it in if you want.  You have a virtual spare spell slot in Speed of Vallon.  I used to just use my epic for haste on the pet, but I've bagged it recently, and it's too much of a pain in the ass to pull it out, etc.  Plus I have my HoH lineup saved to a spell set <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="icon_biggrin.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
You really need pacification a bit, you are using it for your initial pet pull and also for your first split on each side.  After that it becomes relatively redundant.  And to be honest, you have enough room in that area to run around and get distance for a Sleep, rather than standing there having the shit kicked out of you by a hasted mob trying to get WoM off.  If you have good defensive AA's and maybe CF, you could probably get away with it.  Personally, I would rather not get hit at all.
<br />

<br />
As with all these things, your milage may vary.  What I've documented above is how I do it.  If you want to make changes, feel free.  However, if you do change things, don't blame me if you go splat working out the details of your new strat <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="icon_biggrin.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
Regards,
<br />

