                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I used to camp that left shrine a lot and since there's an even number of spawns and most are in pairs I found it it easiest, safest and the best overall xp to charm 1 from each pair, neither haste nor slow, use nukes to make sure my pet barely wins, then invis and nuke pet to death.  (if your pet's winning by too much you can spam /pet back off so he'll attack less drop his hp down some)
<br />

<br />
From every mob pair I'd get 50% xp from one and 100% xp from the other which is some better than using 1 pet to get 50% xp from many mobs before killing it off.
<br />

<br />
The bonus to this method is charm never needed to last more than 1 fight, so almost never broke on its own.  Plus I didn't have to bother slowing anything or risk being around a hasted pet.
<br />

<br />
It's not as much xp as invising and nuking both pet and the target down but it's very consistent and safe.  You'll almost never have an 'uh oh' moment.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
