                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I just want to say that this camp spot is very very nice. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /> I'm falling into the "haste one pet, have it kill 5, break charm, kill former pet" camp - mostly because that's how I feel most comfortable. I prefer having one chainsaw pet then killing them 1 to 1. Although I could see how that would work nicely as well. 
<br />

<br />
The only problem is that when charm breaks happen, they HAPPEN. I just went through a string of FOUR charm breaks on a single pet before I just cycled him for a sentry. And how much of a pita are those unrootable sentries? <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
But with a Haste of Solusek effect, no other casting haste buffs, and no extended range item, I can charm a mob with CoD by chain clicking charm until they get in range. The spell usually goes off with Mr Shiny Pants about 10 feet in front of me. So I'm pretty much spinning 360 in place to make sure I don't get a last second interrupt on my spell.
<br />

<br />
Anyhoo, thanks again for the great spot. One cycle down, one spec parchment looted, and 6 percent xp at level 64. Good times. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
