                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I know I'm odd among chanters, but in HoH at least I prefer to find a good pet and keep him.  I find that if I do the "run one pet until he's low and then kill him" strat, then I not only get kinda LoM but end up having stuff spawn all out of order.  That disorder means that I'm less free to kite and the next spawn can be in a very inconvenient spot.  Not only that, but I hate having to recast root when Insanity breaks it and having to kite two mobs in case of an early charm break.
<br />

<br />
So, I charm kill "normally" until I get a good solid Guardian or Sentry.  Then I just keep him.  When he gets to about 20% health, I'll break charm with <a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=27830" target="_blank" class="postlink">Tae Ew Ritualist's Mask</a> at a decent distance and mez him.  Then it's tash and mem blur.  After about 30 seconds he'll be full health again, and I can CoD at leisure. Mez casts much faster than CoD, so there's a bigger safety margin when CH'ing the pet.  Also, all the respawns happen in the same order, so I always know where to go and where not to go.
<br />

<br />
If I'm feeling zany, I can still get the full xp for a kill by breaking charm, mezing pet, and nuking down the target mob right when I'm going to CH the pet anyway.
<br />

<br />
I like the fun of chaos as much as the next guy, but why make things more complex than they need to be, I ask?
<br />

<br />
P.S. Don't worry Qenya, I always recant the pets before I leave the Shrine to you.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="icon_biggrin.gif" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
P.P.S.  Sentries hit for 580+ rather than the 544 max from Guardians.  I keep the Sentries as pets for that reason.  Since I'm CH'ing them anyway, I don't mind mezing them when charm breaks.
<br />

<br />
-Brilynz</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=58295&alt=0" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://benlevin.home.mindspring.com/BrilDragonSig1a.jpg" border="0" /></a>
<br />
<a href="http://www.therunes.net/forums/viewtopic.php?p=18979" target="_blank" class="postlink">Enchanter Code v0.2</a>:
<br />
E65.160/Pr h++ 3.27khp 4.88hm ft15 !G e++(+++) o++ T+ L- H+++ f g- b c++++ t++ D- !X</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
